-      <h3>Orbit, zoom, and automatic spin</h3>
-      <p>Drag anywhere on the cube stage to orbit around the puzzle. Use a mouse wheel to zoom, or pinch with two fingers on a touchscreen. The <strong>Spin</strong> slider continuously orbits the camera: negative values rotate counter-clockwise, positive values rotate clockwise, and <code>0</code> turns spin off. Auto-spin pauses while you are dragging and continues during turns, algorithms, scrambles, and pattern playback.</p>
-
-      <h3>Face-turn buttons and notation</h3>
-      <p>The twelve move buttons turn the six faces clockwise or counter-clockwise: <code>U D L R F B</code>. Read a plain letter as clockwise while looking directly at that face. A prime mark (<code>'</code>) means counter-clockwise, and <code>2</code> means one smooth 180-degree half turn. The move engine also supports middle slices <code>M E S</code> and whole-cube rotations <code>x y z</code> when they appear in algorithms and patterns.</p>
-      <p>Every move passes through one queue, so button presses, keyboard turns, guide algorithms, scrambles, and patterns play in order without overlapping. The large move HUD at the top flashes the token currently being performed.</p>
-
-      <h3>Keyboard shortcuts</h3>
-      <p>Press <code>U</code>, <code>D</code>, <code>L</code>, <code>R</code>, <code>F</code>, or <code>B</code> for a clockwise face turn; hold <strong>Shift</strong> for the prime version. Press <strong>Escape</strong> to close an open TECH or HELP overlay. When no overlay is open, Escape toggles the solving guide.</p>
-
-      <h3>Scramble, Solve, and Reset</h3>
-      <p><strong>SCRAMBLE</strong> performs 22 fast random face turns and never chooses the same face twice in succession. It also clears the visible pattern sequence strip.</p>
-      <p><strong>SOLVE</strong> works from any state created in CUBED—including manual turns, scrambles, guide algorithms, stacked patterns, slice moves, and whole-cube rotations. It cancels moves and patterns that have not yet begun, allows a turn already in motion to finish safely, then animates the exact inverse sequence back to solved. The solution appears in the sequence strip as <strong>AUTO SOLVE</strong>. Manual turns, Scramble, patterns, and guide Play buttons are temporarily ignored while solving; RESET can stop the process immediately.</p>
-      <p><strong>RESET</strong> clears queued moves, waiting patterns, and solution history; lets any turn already in motion finish safely; rebuilds a perfectly solved cube; and clears the sequence strip. Reset keeps your currently selected color palette.</p>
-
-      <h3>Pattern gallery and sequence playback</h3>
